      h1(data-device-preview="../docs-demos/buttons.html") Buttons
      p Framework7 comes with a bunch of ready to use buttons. All you need is to just add appropriate classes to your links or submit/button inputs:
      h3 Usual Buttons
      p Just add <code>button</code> class to any link or button input:
      pre
        code
          | &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="#" class="button"&gt;Usual Button 1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
          | &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="#" class="button"&gt;Usual Button 2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
          | &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="#" class="button"&gt;Usual Button 3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;          
      .important-note
        p Note that, by default, each button in Framework7 is "display:block" and will take 100% of its parent width. 
      h3 Active State
      p Just add additional <code>active</code> class to button:
      pre
        code
          | &lt;a href="#" class="button active"&gt;Active Button&lt;/a&gt;

      h3 Round Buttons
      p Add additional <code>button-round</code> class to button:
      pre
        code
          | &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="#" class="button button-round"&gt;Round Button 1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
          | &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="#" class="button button-round"&gt;Round Button 2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
          | &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="#" class="button button-round active"&gt;Round Button Active&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;          
      h3 Big Buttons
      p Add additional <code>button-big</code> class to button:
      pre
        code
          | &lt;a href="#" class="button button-big"&gt;Big Button &lt;/a&gt;
          | &lt;a href="#" class="button button-big button-round"&gt;Big Round Button &lt;/a&gt;
          | &lt;a href="#" class="button button-big button-round active"&gt;Big Round Active Button &lt;/a&gt;          
      h3 Buttons Row / Segmented Control
      .important-note
        p <strong>Note that each button has equal width when in "buttons-row"</strong>
      p Just wrap buttons with element with <code>buttons-row</code> class:
        pre
          code
            | &lt;p class="buttons-row"&gt;
            |   &lt;a href="#" class="button"&gt;Button 1&lt;/a&gt;
            |   &lt;a href="#" class="button"&gt;Button 2&lt;/a&gt;
            |   &lt;a href="#" class="button"&gt;Button 3&lt;/a&gt;
            | &lt;/p&gt;
            | &lt;p class="buttons-row"&gt;
            |   &lt;a href="#" class="button active"&gt;Button 1&lt;/a&gt;
            |   &lt;a href="#" class="button"&gt;Button 2&lt;/a&gt;
            |   &lt;a href="#" class="button"&gt;Button 3&lt;/a&gt;
            | &lt;/p&gt;
            | &lt;p class="buttons-row"&gt;
            |   &lt;a href="#" class="button button-round"&gt;Button 1&lt;/a&gt;
            |   &lt;a href="#" class="button button-round"&gt;Button 2&lt;/a&gt;
            | &lt;/p&gt;
            | &lt;p class="buttons-row"&gt;
            |   &lt;a href="#" class="button button-round"&gt;Button 1&lt;/a&gt;
            |   &lt;a href="#" class="button button-round active"&gt;Button 2&lt;/a&gt;
            | &lt;/p&gt;            
      h3 Fill Buttons
      p Fill Buttons looks almost the same as active but indended to be used as single buttons which also have a bit different effect on click/tap:
      pre
        code
          | &lt;a href="#" class="button button-fill"&gt;Fill Button &lt;/a&gt;
          | &lt;a href="#" class="button button-round button-fill"&gt;Round Fill Button&lt;/a&gt;
          | &lt;a href="#" class="button button-big button-fill"&gt;Big Fill Button &lt;/a&gt;
      h3 Color Buttons
      p You can use 10 default <a href="color-themes.html">color themes</a> to colorize buttons
      pre
        code
          | &lt;p class="buttons-row theme-pink"&gt;
          |     &lt;a href="#" class="button active"&gt;Button 1&lt;/a&gt;
          |     &lt;a href="#" class="button"&gt;Button 2&lt;/a&gt;
          |     &lt;a href="#" class="button"&gt;Button 3&lt;/a&gt;
          | &lt;/p&gt;
          | &lt;p class="buttons-row theme-orange"&gt;
          |     &lt;a href="#" class="button"&gt;Button 1&lt;/a&gt;
          |     &lt;a href="#" class="button active"&gt;Button 2&lt;/a&gt;
          |     &lt;a href="#" class="button"&gt;Button 3&lt;/a&gt;
          | &lt;/p&gt;
          | &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="#" class="button button-fill color-green"&gt;Green&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
          | &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="#" class="button button-fill color-red button-round"&gt;Round Red&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
          | &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="#" class="button button-big button-fill color-gray"&gt;Big Gray&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
          | &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="#" class="button button-fill button-big color-yellow"&gt;Big Yellow&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;          
      h3 List Block Buttons
      p We can use buttons with our favourite <a href="list-view.html">List Views</a>:
      pre
        code
          | &lt;div class="content-block-title"&gt;List block buttons&lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;div class="list-block"&gt;
          |   &lt;ul&gt;
          |     &lt;li&gt;
          |       &lt;a href="#" class="item-link list-button"&gt;List Button 1&lt;/a&gt;
          |     &lt;/li&gt;
          |     &lt;li&gt;
          |       &lt;a href="#" class="item-link list-button"&gt;List Button 2&lt;/a&gt;
          |     &lt;/li&gt;
          |     &lt;li&gt;
          |       &lt;a href="#" class="item-link list-button"&gt;List Button 3&lt;/a&gt;
          |     &lt;/li&gt;
          |   &lt;/ul&gt;
          | &lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;div class="content-block-title"&gt;Inset list block buttons&lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;div class="list-block inset"&gt;
          |   &lt;ul&gt;
          |     &lt;li&gt;
          |       &lt;a href="#" class="item-link list-button"&gt;List Button 1&lt;/a&gt;
          |     &lt;/li&gt;
          |     &lt;li&gt;
          |       &lt;a href="#" class="item-link list-button"&gt;List Button 2&lt;/a&gt;
          |     &lt;/li&gt;
          |     &lt;li&gt;
          |       &lt;a href="#" class="item-link list-button"&gt;List Button 3&lt;/a&gt;
          |     &lt;/li&gt;
          |   &lt;/ul&gt;
          | &lt;/div&gt;          
      h3 Using Grid
      p And of course, you can place buttons anywhere where you want and need. Here is example using <a href="grid.html">Grid</a>:
      pre
        code
          | &lt;div class="row"&gt;
          |   &lt;div class="col-50"&gt;
          |     &lt;a href="#" class="button button-big button-fill color-red"&gt;Cancel&lt;/a&gt;
          |   &lt;/div&gt;
          |   &lt;div class="col-50"&gt;
          |     &lt;a href="#" class="button button-big button-fill color-green"&gt;Submit&lt;/a&gt;
          |   &lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;/div&gt;          